President Trump delivered remarks at the Grand Hyatt Hotel in Seoul, South Korea. He expressed gratitude for the strong relationship between the US and South Korea and praised Ambassador Harris for his leadership. Trump also discussed the progress made with North Korea, emphasizing the improved relationship and the steps taken to reduce nuclear and ballistic tests and secure the release of hostages. He highlighted the economic ties between the US and South Korea, including the renegotiated trade deal and increased investment in the US by Korean companies. Trump also mentioned the success of his pro-growth policies, such as tax cuts and deregulation, and the positive impact on the US economy. He emphasized the importance of fair and reciprocal trade relationships and the need to further reduce the trade deficit. Trump concluded by expressing his optimism for the future of the US-South Korea alliance and his intention to visit the DMZ to potentially meet with Chairman Kim of North Korea.